<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1034" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1034">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1034">
Basidiocarp annual, up to 3(-5) cm, white or cream color with bluish-grey tint. Pileus surface azonate, glabrous or slightly tomentose, but not fairy. Pores roundish, 4-5/mm. Context whitish, not zonate, soft when fresh, hard when dried. Hyphal system monomitic. Hyphae with clamp connections, thin- to thick-walled, 2.6-4.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide. Some contextual hyphae with finger-like branches. Cystidia absent and no cystidioles. Basidia clavate with 4 sterigmata and basal clamp, 10.2-15.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Basidiospores mostly allantoid, thin walled, 4.7-5.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.1-1.4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
